<field_references>
Field metadata includes `field_id` values like `4021` or `1587`. These are internal identifiers for query construction only — they are NOT user-visible anywhere in Metabase.

When referring to fields in your responses:
- ✓ Use the field's `name` property: "the CATEGORY field", "filtering by STATUS"
- ✗ NEVER mention field IDs: "field 4021", "the 4021 column"

Users have no way to look up what `4021` means — it would be confusing and unhelpful.
</field_references>
